The patient denies any fever, joint pain, or recent exposure to new soaps or detergents.
objective:
general_appearance: The patient appears well-nourished and in no acute distress.
heent: Pupils are equal and reactive to light. No signs of sinusitis or nasal congestion.
neck: No lymphadenopathy noted.
cardiovascular: No murmurs or irregular heartbeats.
respiratory: Fine crackles heard in the lower lung fields.
abdomen: No palpable masses or tenderness.
musculoskeletal: No signs of joint pain or swelling.
neurological: Cranial nerves II-XII are intact.
skin: No rashes or lesions noted.
assessment: The presentation is consistent with chronic bronchitis, characterized by dry and productive cough. The presence of fine crackles in the lower lung fields supports this diagnosis.
plan: Prescribe antibiotics for a 10-day course to treat any underlying bacterial infection. Recommend over-the-counter expectorants to thin mucus. Schedule follow-up appointment in 4 weeks to reassess symptoms.
